data.title: 8 Detainees in West Bank at dawn Thursday
data.meta_description: The occupation forces arrested at least eight citi...
data.text:
The occupation forces arrested at least eight citizens at dawn today, Thursday, from Tulkarm, Ramallah and Bethlehem.

And local sources said that the occupation arrested the young man, Muhammad Samer Mahmoud Jaber (21 years), from Nour Shams camp, east of Tulkarm.

In the city of Nablus, university student Obadah Sahir Abu Sir was arrested, after raiding his familyÂ´s home, searching him and terrorizing the family, in the Jisr al-Titi area in the northern mountainous region, and confiscated mobile phones and computers.

The occupation also arrested the young Moataz Zebar from the town of Kober, north of Ramallah, after they raided his house and searched it, and the two young men, Ahmed Mutair and Anas Al-Khatib, from Qalandia camp north of Jerusalem.

From Bethlehem, the Israeli occupation forces arrested two former prisoners, Imad Ali Al-Harimi (19 years), from Al-Saff Street, and Jibril Khalil Kawazbeh (25 years), from Al-Fawaghra neighborhood in Bethlehem.

The occupation forces also arrested Majed Salem Abu Zahra (50 years), from the town of Yatta, south of Hebron.
